	(1204,'Elizabeth',NULL,'Strutt','Frost (maiden name); Byron (second married name)','F',1782,1867,'Writer.  In 1863, the government granted her a literary pension of £70 per year \"in consideration of her straightened circumstances at a great age and after fifty-eight years of contributions to literature.\"  See entry in DNB.','Allibone; DNB'),
